[Black "Chapter 2 Scheveningen Formation"]

{In Chapters 2 and 3, Black establishes the modest e6/d6 central pawn duo that resembles the Scheveningen structure, one of Black's most solid and flexible defensive systems in the Open Sicilian.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 d6 6. Bc4 e6 {[%entry]} 7. O-O Be7 8. Qe2 Nf6 9. Rd1 e5 (9... Qc7 10. Nb5 Qb8 11. Bf4 e5 (11... Ne5 12. Nxd6+ (12. Rxd6) 12... Bxd6 13. Rxd6 Qxd6 14. Bxe5) 12. Bg5 a6 (12... O-O 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 (13... gxf6? 14. Nh4) 14. Nxd6) 13. Bxf6 axb5 (13... gxf6 14. Nc3) 14. Bxe7 Kxe7) (9... Bd7 10. Nb5 (10. Bf4) 10... Qb8 11. Bf4 Ne5 12. Nxd6+ (12. Rxd6) 12... Bxd6 13. Rxd6 Qxd6 14. Nxe5) 10. Be3 (10. h3) 10... O-O 11. Rac1 Bd7 (11... Bg4 12. h3 Bh5 13. g4 Bg6 14. Nh4 Rc8 15. Nf5) (11... Be6 12. b4 a6 (12... Nxb4 13. Nxe5) 13. a3 Rc8 14. Bxe6 fxe6 15. Qa2) (11... Ng4) 12. a3 a6 13. b4 *
